## Development Commands

### Backend (Strapi)
```bash
cd backend
npm install              # Install dependencies
npm run develop          # Start Strapi dev server (:1337)
npm run build            # Build Strapi admin panel
npm run start            # Start production server
npm run strapi generate  # Generate content types, APIs
```

### Frontend (Astro)
```bash
cd frontend
npm install              # Install dependencies
npm run dev              # Dev server (http://localhost:4321)
npm run build            # Build for production
npm run preview          # Preview production build
```

## Git Workflow

- **Main branch**: `{{GIT_MAIN_BRANCH}}` вЂ” production, never commit directly
- **Integration branch**: `{{GIT_INTEGRATION_BRANCH}}` вЂ” feature branches merge here
- **Feature branches**: `feature/<description>` from `{{GIT_INTEGRATION_BRANCH}}`
- **Hotfix branches**: `hotfix/<description>` from `{{GIT_MAIN_BRANCH}}`

## Coding Conventions

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode; no `any` type; define interfaces for all API responses
- Use discriminated unions for complex state
- Prefer `type` for unions/intersections, `interface` for object shapes

### Astro
- Use `.astro` files for static components (default)
- Use React/Vue/Svelte only for interactive islands (`client:load`, `client:visible`, `client:idle`)
- Keep frontmatter (`---`) minimal; extract complex logic to `lib/`
- Use `getStaticPaths()` for dynamic routes in SSG mode

### Strapi
- Define content types via the Content-Type Builder or JSON schema
- Use controllers for custom business logic, services for reusable operations
- Use lifecycle hooks for side effects (email on publish, cache invalidation)
- REST API is the primary integration method

### General
- 2-space indentation; single quotes for strings
- Early returns to reduce nesting
- Mobile-first responsive design with Tailwind CSS

## Security Requirements

**Never read, display, or include the contents of these files:**

| Category | Files / Patterns |
|----------|-----------------|
| Environment | `.env`, `.env.*`, `.env.local`, `.env.*.local` вЂ” `.env.example` is safe |
| Keys & certs | `*.key`, `*.pem`, `*.p12`, `*.pfx`, `*.crt`, `*.cer` |
| Credentials | `auth.json`, `credentials.json`, `*service-account*.json` |
| Cloud auth | `.aws/credentials`, `.aws/config`, `.azure/` |
| SSH / Git | `.ssh/`, `.git-credentials`, `.netrc` |
| Secrets | `secrets.yml`, `vault.yml`, any file with `secret` or `token` in name |
| Database | `backend/database/*.db`, `backend/database/*.sqlite` |

**Hard rules:**
- Astro `PUBLIC_` prefixed env vars are bundled into the client вЂ” never use this prefix for secrets
- Strapi API tokens and admin credentials must never appear in code or responses
- Never include API keys or tokens in code examples or responses
- Verify `.gitignore` covers `.env` variants and `database/` before staging

## Important Notes

- `node_modules/`, `.astro/`, `dist/`, and `backend/build/` are generated вЂ” never edit or commit them
- Strapi admin requires first-time user creation at `/admin`
- API permissions must be configured in Strapi admin > Settings > Users & Permissions > Roles
- Strapi returns relative media URLs; prepend `STRAPI_URL` in frontend
- See `CLAUDE.md` for Claude Code-specific workflow skills and the memory system
